  "prompt": "What is the formula to calculate a synchronous speed of a motor?",
  "response": "The synchronous speed of a motor can be calculated using the following formula:\n\n\\[ n_s = \\frac{120 \\times f}{P} \\]\n\nWhere:\n- \\( n_s \\) is the synchronous speed in revolutions per minute (RPM),\n- \\( f \\) is the frequency of the power supply in hertz (Hz),\n- \\( P \\) is the number of poles in the motor.\n\nThis formula is derived from the relationship between the rotational speed of the magnetic field and the frequency of the alternating current supplying the motor.",
